Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @carrot{1}, then slice into 1cm thick rounds (no need to peel).

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}(zested and halved).

Pour the @water{300%ml}(for the rice) into a #medium saucepan{} with a #tight-fitting lid{}.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the #lid{}.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, in a #large bowl{}, combine the garlic, @Thai style spice mix{1}(add less if you'd prefer things milder), @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp}(for the breadcrumbs), then add the @British beef mince{240%g}.

Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll into even-sized balls, 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the meatballs onto a #large baking tray{}.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the sliced carrot and season with salt and pepper. Fry, stirring frequently, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir in the @red Thai style paste{50%g} and cook ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{50%ml}(for the curry).

Mix together well, then bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{6-7%minutes}. Add a splash of water if it gets too thick.

Once the curry has thickened, remove from the heat and stir through the cooked meatballs. Squeeze in half the lime juice, then taste and add more lime juice, salt and pepper if needed.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, stir through the lime zest, then spoon into your #bowls{}.

Top with your red Thai inspired meatball curry. Enjoy!